Cross-domain fusion

This is where your idea gets bigger than a single app.

You want one domain-agnostic preference representation.

A person’s choices in:
	•	dating
	•	collectibles
	•	food
	•	design
	•	entertainment
	•	fashion
	•	politics
	•	habit formation

can all map into one deeper structure.

Not by pretending they are identical,
but by learning shared latent dimensions.

Example:
	•	novelty-seeking may show up in dating, music, fashion, and investments
	•	scarcity sensitivity may show up in collectibles, shopping, and status preferences
	•	comfort preference may show up in aesthetics, partner choices, and media habits

So the architecture should support:

domain-specific signals -> domain embeddings -> shared latent human vector

That means:
	•	one layer learns the local domain
	•	another layer learns cross-domain invariants

This is how you get “human nature” out of fragmented app data.

